Add SQLRepositoryEvent implementation with UUID support
Implemented SQLRepositoryEvent class that provides CRUD operations for Event entities with UUID identifiers. The implementation includes:
- Proper exception handling with ValidationException and RepositoryException - Resource management using try-with-resources - UUID collision detection in the generateEvent method - Comprehensive logging with Log4j - Connection management through JdbcUtils - Full CRUD operations: findOne, findAll, add, update, and delete
All methods validate input parameters and handle database operations safely with proper resource cleanup.
